.
 To complete the QW, we need to repeat the whole cycle many times.
 It is emphasized that the auxiliary state 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|a\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 which is introduced for temporal shelving is empty when the six-step cycle
 is completed.
 It means there is no probability to find the ion at the state 
