\begin_layout Section
DYNAMICS OF BOUND STATE
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:5"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the Sec.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "sec:4"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we have verified the existence of bound states when interfering with non-trivi
al bulk.
 In this section we study the dynamics of bound state under time-varying
 bulk parameters, both quenching and slow but non-adiabatic process.
 Notice that under these process, the unitary dynamcis will not change system's
 topological invariant 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "caio2015quantum,d2015dynamical"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Instead of preparing the system onto ground state as suggested in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "xu2018measuringd"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, here steady-state wave function first build in one phase, which character
 as 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\text{Loc}}$
\end_inset

.
 The idea of time-dependent coin operation have been mentioned in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "PhysRevA.73.062304,PhysRevLett.104.050502"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, while neither dealing with bound state.
 Here we show how bound states (steady-state) response to different dynamical
 process (further with disorder).
 
\color red
We also study how changing time-frame and breaking symmetry effects bound
 state -> Maybe put this into sup.
 inf.

\color inherit
 
\end_layout

