) has the form:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\theta_{1}(t)=\begin{cases}
\theta_{1}^{i} & t\leq t_{0}-\tau\\
\frac{\theta_{1}^{i}+\theta_{1}^{f}}{2}+\frac{\theta_{1}^{f}-\theta_{1}^{i}}{2}\tanh(\frac{t-t_{0}}{\xi}) & t_{0}-\tau<t\leq t_{0}+\tau\\
\theta_{1}^{f} & t_{0}+\tau<t
\end{cases},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

 determine the speed of evolution between two phases.
 The evolution tend to be the quench process with small 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

; and to be the adiabatic evolution with large 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

.
 First 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{0}-\tau$
\end_inset

 steps for buliding steady-state with 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}^{i}$
\end_inset

.
 Final steps after 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{0}+\tau$
\end_inset

 for buliding steady-state with 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}^{f}$
\end_inset

.
 We still character our system with 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\text{Loc}}$
\end_inset

.
 In Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:5"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we simulate dynamics between neighbor regions.
 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{0}$
\end_inset

 is 40 steps and 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

 is 20 steps here.
 In second row of Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:5"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we fix 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{2}=\pi/2$
\end_inset

, first study the situation with the neighbor regions.
 We evolve 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}$
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi/4$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $3\pi/4$
\end_inset

, which correspond to transfer from 
\begin_inset Formula $(1,1)$
\end_inset

 to (
\begin_inset Formula $1,0)$
\end_inset

 (red star to green star) and the inverse process.
 So we can study how bound states evolve to another non-trivial phase.
 We can easily observe from the simulation result that bound state exists
 after transferring to another non-trivial phase regardless of evolution
 velocity (similar between 
