Here we study the condition when the evolution across phase boundary twice.
 In this condition, two phases are not adjacent.
 We set fixed 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}=\pi/4$
\end_inset

, then transfer 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{2}$
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi/2$
