\begin_layout Section
Sign of bound state
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:B"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "fig:sup_2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, the signs of bound state is shown.
 Wave fuction in 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,1)$
\end_inset

 with a single 
\begin_inset Formula $E=\pi$
\end_inset

 bound is predicted to appear a minus signs after each steps, while in 
\begin_inset Formula $(1,0)$
\end_inset

 with a single 
\begin_inset Formula $E=0$
\end_inset

 bound state will not.
 After several steps building up steady-state, the signs at 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|0\right\rangle \otimes\left|\downarrow\right\rangle ,\left|0\right\rangle \otimes\left|\uparrow\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 also become stable.
 In 
\begin_inset Formula $(1,0)$
\end_inset

, the signs of (
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\downarrow\right\rangle ,\left|\uparrow\right\rangle $
\end_inset

) are always 
\begin_inset Formula $(-+)$
\end_inset

 however in 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,1)$
\end_inset

 the signs will change between 
\begin_inset Formula $(--)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(++),$
\end_inset

 which agrees the discussion above.
 So different single bound state could be distinguish.
 What's more, as interference patterns of the region with two boundary will
 appear and no boundary state at the vacuum phase.
