\begin_layout Section
High dimensional QW
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:D"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Two dimensional QW suggested in Ref.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "PhysRevA.82.033429,chen2018observation,yan2019strongly,sajid2019creating,li2020two"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, which could be associated with non-trivial Chern numbers and more complex
 Floquet band structure.
 This idea could also be realized based on our proposal.
 Single step with two coin operations and two walk operations:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
U=S_{y}R(\theta_{2})S_{x}R(\theta_{1}),
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{x}=\sum_{x,y}\left|x+1,y\right\rangle \left\langle x,y\right|\otimes\left|\uparrow\right\rangle \left\langle \uparrow\right|+\left|x-1,y\right\rangle \left\langle x,y\right|\otimes\left|\downarrow\right\rangle \left\langle \downarrow\right|$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{y}=\sum_{x,y}\left|x,y+1\right\rangle \left\langle x,y\right|\otimes\left|\uparrow\right\rangle \left\langle \uparrow\right|+\left|x,y-1\right\rangle \left\langle x,y\right|\otimes\left|\downarrow\right\rangle \left\langle \downarrow\right|$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $x,y$
\end_inset

 are independent freedoms here.
 
\begin_inset Formula $R(\theta)$
\end_inset

 also means rotation of the spin around y axis by angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 here.
 Based on this proposal, CS bound state can exist at the interface of Floquet
 insulators even whose Chern numbers vanish, which is the unique phenomena
 in Periodically driven systems 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Kitagawa2012,chen2018observation"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 In our proposal, two dimensions of the particle propagation are encoded
 onto two motional modes of a single trapped ion: for example, the axis
 mode and radial mode with cooling and resolved frequency 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{z},\omega_{r}$
\end_inset

.
 What's more, Raman beams are needed in both axis and radial direction.
 Based on the former 1D SSQW proposal and set 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{2}=0$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{x,y}R(\theta)$
\end_inset

 can be realized with suitable Raman beams detuning of motional modes.
 Of course, this 2D model has two reflecting boundary for 
\begin_inset Formula $x,y\geq0$
\end_inset

.
 Based on this idea, arbitrary dimensional quantum walk can be realized.
 More motional modes will enlarge the motional space in the high dimensional
 QW with the ability of resolved sideband transition.
 And this high dimensional quantum walk (more than 2D) can not be reached
 in the system which walk state is encoded on position or path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Dynamics under different time frame and symmetry
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:E"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here we study the condition which (
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1},\theta_{2}$
\end_inset

) does not change while quenching to another time-frame or suddenly inducing
 operation to break the symmetry.
 In first plot of Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:sup_4"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we study the dynamics of the bound state when suddenly quenching to another
 time frame: 1) change order of 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1},\theta_{2}$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $U(\theta_{2},\theta_{1})$
\end_inset

 2) change to the first time frame preserve CS: 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{1}(\theta_{1},\theta_{2})$
\end_inset

 3)
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
